{"type":"message","id":"aec54072","parentId":"616e0714","timestamp":"2026-03-23T18:45:40.503Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_tdclb8xurqkt_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-23 144513\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals, the main pending action is the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Experiment:\r\n- [ ] Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- [ ] Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- [ ] Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe insight is that compression and causal discovery are the same problem. I should start implementing the TIC experiment.\r\n\r\nA good first step would be to create a script or document that outlines how to implement the TIC classifier. Let me look at what files exist and what would be the most useful next action.\r\n\r\nI should:\r\n1. Look at existing pulse logs to understand their structure\r\n2. Create the TIC classifier implementation\r\n\r\nLet me create an implementation script for the TIC classifier. This advances the Phase 1 advancement goal directly.\r\n\r\nActually, let me think about what specific file edit would be most useful. The most concrete action would be to create the TIC classifier implementation that can:\r\n1. Parse pulse logs\r\n2. Identify invariants (patterns that persist across multiple pulses)\r\n3. Identify variants (patterns that change)\r\n4. Test classification accuracy\r\n\r\nI'll create a PowerShell script for the TIC classifier since the system uses PowerShell (pulse.ps1).\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment is the critical next step to validate the compression-causal duality hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariants vs variants across pulse logs.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier script to analyze pulse logs and measure invariant/variant classification accuracy against the success criteria (>70% classification, >60% next-pulse prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC: Temporal Invariance Compression Classifier\r\n# Tests compression-causal duality hypothesis\r\n# Success: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$MinOccurrence = 3,\r\n    [float]$InvarianceThreshold = 0.6\r\n)\r\n\r\n$LogsDir = \"logs\"\r\n$OutputFile = \"research/TIC_RESULTS.md\"\r\n\r\n# --- Step 1: Collect pulse logs ---\r\n$pulseFiles = Get-ChildItem \"$LogsDir/pulse_*.md\" | Sort-Object Name | Select-Object -Last 20\r\nif ($pulseFiles.Count -lt 5) {\r\n    Write-Host \"Need at least 5 pulse logs, found $($pulseFiles.Count)\"\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"Analyzing $($pulseFiles.Count) pulse logs...\"\r\n\r\n# --- Step 2: Extract patterns from each pulse ---\r\n$patterns = @{}\r\n$allPatterns = @()\r\n\r\nforeach ($file in $pulseFiles) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $file.FullName -Raw\r\n    # Extract key patterns: headers, bullet points, file references\r\n    $lines = $content -split \"`n\"\r\n    foreach ($line in $lines) {\r\n        if ($line -match '^#{1,3}\\s+(.+)$') {\r\n            $pattern = $matches[1].Trim().ToLower()\r\n            if ($pattern.Length -gt 5) {\r\n                $allPatterns += [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n                    Pulse = $file.Name\r\n                    Pattern = $pattern\r\n                    Type = \"header\"\r\n                }\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        elseif ($line -match '^\\-\\s+(.+)$') {\r\n            $pattern = $matches[1].Trim().ToLower()\r\n            if ($pattern.Length -gt 5) {\r\n                $allPatterns += [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n                    Pulse = $file.Name\r\n                    Pattern = $pattern\r\n                    Type = \"bullet\"\r\n                }\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# --- Step 3: Calculate invariance scores ---\r\n$patternStats = $allPatterns | Group-Object Pattern | ForEach-Object {\r\n    $occurrences = $_.Group | Select-Object -ExpandProperty Pulse -Unique\r\n    [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n        Pattern = $_.Name\r\n        Count = $_.Count\r\n        Pulses = ($occurrences | Measure-Object).Count\r\n        InvarianceScore = $_.Count / $pulseFiles.Count\r\n        Type = ($_.Group | Select-Object -First 1).Type\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# --- Step 4: Classify invariants vs variants ---\r\n$invariants = $patternStats | Where-Object { $_.InvarianceScore -ge $InvarianceThreshold }\r\n$variants = $patternStats | Where-Object { $_.InvarianceScore -lt $InvarianceThreshold }\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"Found $($invariants.Count) invariants, $($variants.Count) variants\"\r\n\r\n# --- Step 5: Test next-pulse prediction ---\r\n# Predict using top invariants as \"expected\" patterns\r\n$predictionCorrect = 0\r\n$predictionTotal = 0\r\n\r\nfor ($i = 5; $i -lt $pulseFiles.Count; $i++) {\r\n    $trainSet = $pulseFiles[0..($i-1)]\r\n    $testFile = $pulseFiles[$i]\r\n    \r\n    # Build expected patterns from training\r\n    $trainPatterns = @()\r\n    foreach ($f in $trainSet) {\r\n        $c = Get-Content $f.FullName -Raw\r\n        $trainPatterns += ($c -split \"`n\") -match '^\\-\\s+' | ForEach-Object { $_.Trim().ToLower() }\r\n    }\r\n    $trainUnique = $trainPatterns | Group-Object | Where-Object { $_.Count -ge 2 } | Select-Object -ExpandProperty Name\r\n    \r\n    # Check test file\r\n    $testContent = Get-Content $testFile.FullName -Raw\r\n    $testBullets = ($testContent -split \"`\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 14:45:35\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774291540500}}
